P450 3A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/140024/', '', 'Mometasone furoate, Amcinonide, Fluocinolone acetonide, Hydrocortisone butyrate, Hydrocortisone, Fluocinonide, Methylprednisolone, Prednisolone, Betamethasone, Fluorometholone, Triamcinolone, More', 'Rifamycin, Kanamycin, Amphotericin B, Polymyxin B, Nystatin, Vancomycin, Streptomycin, Fidaxomicin, Rifaximin, Paromomycin, Neomycin, More', 1767369485);
